sql:
SELECT AVG(perceptions_of_corruption) AS avg_perceptions_of_corruption
FROM happiness_scores
WHERE year = 2022;

SELECT DISTINCT users.user_name
FROM users
JOIN access_logs ON users.user_id = access_logs.user_id;

SELECT ladder_score
FROM happiness_scores
WHERE year IN (2000, 2010, 2020);

external_knowledge:
Higher-ups refer to users with the 'admin' role;
Substantial data files are those larger than the average size of published files;
Typical size refers to the average file size of published versions.

sql:
SELECT explained_id, log_gdp_per_capita, social_support
FROM explained_by
WHERE log_gdp_per_capita > 1.2 AND social_support < 0.9;

SELECT country_id, year 
FROM happiness_scores
ORDER BY year DESC;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT country_id) AS country_count
FROM happiness_scores
WHERE ladder_score > 7.0;

external_knowledge:
- "best happiness scores" refers to the highest ladder scores recorded for each regional indicator;
- "since the turn of the century" means the data considered starts from the year 2000;
- "top-ranked" means the country with the highest ladder score in each regional indicator, breaking ties by the most recent year of scoring.
